page.title: 01Cobham Park and west Strood
page.content: The area is mainly rural, including a high proportion of deciduous woodland. Cobham Park occupies about half of the area. It is quite hilly and largely uncultivated. Nearly 0.1 of the total area is made up of orchards, belonging to a small number of farms. The A2 passes through the area (west to east) and the M2 begins in the area. There is no significant industry. Places of interest include Cobham Hall, Gad's Hill, the site of a Roman villa and the small village of Shorne Ridgeway. A small residential part of Strood is included to the south-east of the area.
